The Trust may make a grant to an applicant only if:
The applicant meets the qualifications required by this subtitle;
The grant is to be used only for the acquisition of interests or rights in real property for recreational or preservation purposes;
The Department approves the project as being in conformity with the Department's criteria governing land acquired under a State grant from Program Open Space;
The trustees of the Trust approve the grant; and
The Board of Public Works approves the grant.
